Direct Known Subclasses:
CalculateDeriveMarkCollectionInput, CalculateDeriveMarkInput, CalculateDeriveObjectInput, CalculateDeriveSingleMemoFromPair, CalculateEllipseLeastSquares, CalculateEllipsoidLeastSquares, CalculateHistogram, CalculateHistogramMasked, CalculateInputFromDelegate, CalculateInputFromPair, CalculateNumberVoxels, CalculateObjectMask, CalculateOverlap, CalculateOverlapMask, CalculateOverlapMIPBase, CalculatePointsFromOutline, CalculateShellObjectMask
public abstract class FeatureCalculation<S,​T extends FeatureInput>
extends Object
implements ResettableCalculation
Caches the result of a feature, until invalidate() is called.

Implements an equivalence-relation via equals() that checks if two feature-calculations are identical. This allows the user to search through a collection of FeatureCalculation to find one with identical parameters and re-use it.

IMPORTANT NOTE: It is therefore important to make sure every class has a well-defined equals() and hashCode().

Author:
Owen Feehan
